Employee: Thomas Whitfield
Employee ID: EID-6402
Position: Employee Relations Partner
Review Period: January 1, 2024 – December 31, 2024
Manager: Mark Sullivan
Overall Rating: Needs Improvement (2.3 / 5.0)

Compensation Details
Base Salary: $91,200
Annual Bonus Awarded: $0 (not eligible based on rating)
Merit Increase: $0 (frozen per policy)
Performance Improvement Plan: Active (initiated 11/15/2024)

Manager Feedback
Thomas struggled to meet case closure deadlines, with 42% of his cases exceeding the 30-day target. His investigation reports frequently required rework due to missing witness statements and factual inconsistencies. A formal coaching plan was initiated in April, but by October only marginal improvement was observed. Specific incidents include failure to escalate a threat-of-violence report within the required 4-hour window, resulting in a Level 2 policy violation. The Performance Improvement Plan outlines concrete expectations around timeliness, documentation accuracy, and adherence to escalation protocols. Progress will be reviewed biweekly through March 2025.

